  "doc_id": "23093",
  "text": "We previously reported that the transcriptional coactivator Gps2 is necessary for E2 transcription and directly binds to both p300 and E2 [CITATION_1] . E2 association with p300 using bacterially expressed proteins was weak and barely above background [CITATION_2] . Gps2 binding was mapped to residues 134 to 216 on the BPV-1 E2 TAD [CITATION_3] . We hypothesize that the interaction between E2 and Gps2 facilitates complex formation with p300, and this leads to acetylation of lysine 111. This, in turn, may stabilize the association of Brd4 in the transcription complex.",
